text: This is just my opinion, and I am aware that a reason Roblox is doing this is due to copyright. But they could have thought of another way to fix this, such as looking into audio more, instead simply taking the easy way out and making the community more broken than it already is.

Because Roblox is deleting/privating audios over 6 seconds, what is the point in uploading an audio? And, not to mention, once you've uploaded those 10 audios, that is your max for the month, which can be a real pain to new developers who Roblox has not noticed yet.

Talking about MM2 again, in it, there is a gamepass, (I believe 475 Robux), that allows the player to play an audio of their choice, but if Roblox is deleting all audios over 6 seconds, then not only is the gamepass essentially worthless, Roblox is also loosing potential money.
